data.name: bodySizeDescription
data.value: The diameter of the extent of the Quelea's bounds. This is used for collision detection among other things.

data.name: agentDescription
data.value: An autonomous agent that is an extension of a Particle and can percieve its surroundings and make decisions on how to act.

data.name: historyLengthDescription
data.value: The number of past positions to remember for each Quelea.

data.name: lifespanDescription
data.value: Number of timesteps that the Quelea will be alive for. If negative, lifespan will be infinite.

data.name: massDescription
data.value: Affects how strongly the Quelea reacts to forces. Larger masses will lead to more cumbersome movement.

data.name: maxForceDescription
data.value: Steering ability can be controlled by limiting the magnitude of the steering force.

data.name: maxSpeedDescription
data.value: Rather than teleporting, the Quelea will move incrementally by this speed towards targets that it seeks.

data.name: visionAngleDescription
data.value: The maximum angle, taken from the velocity vector, that the Agent can see around it.

data.name: visionRadiusDescription
data.value: The maximum radius around the Agent that it can see.

data.name: alignForceDescription
data.value: Steer towards the average heading of Neighbors.

data.name: coheseForceDescription
data.value: Steer to move toward the average position of neighbors

data.name: constructAgentDescription
data.value: Constructs the settings for an Agent.

data.name: separateForceDescription
data.value: Applies a force to steer to avoid neighbors.

data.name: bodySizeErrorMessage
data.value: Body Size must be greater than or equal to 0.

data.name: maxSpeedErrorMessage
data.value: Maximum Speed must be greater than or equal to 0.

data.name: maxForceErrorMessage
data.value: Maximum Force must be greater than or equal to 0.

data.name: visionAngleErrorMessage
data.value: Vision Angle must be greater than or equal to 0.

data.name: visionRadiusErrorMessage
data.value: Vision Radius must be greater than or equal to 0.

data.name: systemDescription
data.value: Represents a self-contained System of Quelea and Emitters.

data.name: emittersDescription
data.value: Emitters from which the Quelea will be spawned from.

data.name: agentsCountErrorMessage
data.value: There must be at least 1 Agent.

data.name: emittersCountErrorMessage
data.value: There must be at least 1 Emitter.

data.name: AgentSystemType_TypeDescription_An_Agent_System_controls_the_adding__removing__and_updating_of_agents_
data.value: An Agent System controls the adding, removing, and updating of particles.

data.name: AABoxEnvDescription
data.value: A world Axis Aligned Box Environment.

data.name: AABoxDescription
data.value: A Box aligned to World Axes.

data.name: AABoxError
data.value: Box must be aligned to WorldXY.

data.name: behaviorDescription
data.value: A Behavior alters the state of the Quelea.

data.name: neighborsToReactTo
data.value: The neighbors to react to. Use the Get Neighbors in Radius Component.

data.name: bounceContainBehaviorDescription
data.value: Causes Particles to bounce off Environment boundaries.

data.name: bounceContainBehaviorEnvironmentDescription
data.value: The environment which to bounce off of.

data.name: behaviorAppliedDescription
data.value: True iff the behavior was applied to the Quelea.

data.name: boxForEmitterDescription
data.value: Box representing the bounds within which Quelea will be emitted.

data.name: continuousFlowDescription
data.value: If true, particles will be emitted every Rth timestep. If false, N particles will be emitted once.

data.name: creationRateDescription
data.value: Rate at which new Quelea are created. Every Rth timestep.

data.name: numQueleaDescription
data.value: The number of Quelea that are allowed to be alive in the system at once.

data.name: creationRateErrorMessage
data.value: Creation rate must be greater than 0.

data.name: numQueleaErrorMessage
data.value: Number of Quelea must be greater than or equal to 0.

data.name: containForceDescription
data.value: Applies a force to keep Agents away from Environment boundaries.

data.name: visionRadiusMultiplierDescription
data.value: The factor by which the Agent's Vision Radius will be multiplied by. The result will determine how far out the Agent will see other neighbors.

data.name: visionRadiusMultiplierErrorMessage
data.value: Vision Radius Multiplier must be between 0.0 and 1.0.

data.name: deconstructQNDescription
data.value: Deconstructs a Quelea Network into a list of Quelea

data.name: queleaNetworkDescription
data.value: A container object of Quelea to provide for fast lookup of neighbors.

data.name: deconstructQueleaDescription
data.value: Deconstructs a Quelea to expose its position, velocity, and lifespan.

data.name: positionDescription
data.value: The Point3d Position of the Agent.

data.name: velocityDescription
data.value: The direction and magnitude of the Quelea's movement.

data.name: accelerationDescription
data.value: The vector of the Quelea's acceleration.

data.name: positionHistoryDescription
data.value: The past positions of the agent.

data.name: deconstructSystemDescription
data.value: Deconstructs a System to expose its list of Quelea and QueleaNetwork.

data.name: emitterDescription
data.value: The geometry from which Quelea will be spawned.

data.name: environmentDescription
data.value: A geometrical object representing the environment the Quelea will interact with.

data.name: getNeighborsInRadiusDescription
data.value: Gets the Neighbors of an Agent within a specified radius.

data.name: agentToGetNeighborsFor
data.value: The Agent to get neighbors for.

data.name: queleaNetworkToSearch
data.value: The Quelea Network to search through.

data.name: curveEmitterDescription
data.value: A curve from which Quelea can be emitted.

data.name: pointEmitterDescription
data.value: A point from which Quelea can be emitted.

data.name: brepEnvironmentDescription
data.value: A closed Brep Environment which the particles will interact with.

data.name: brepForEnvironmentDescription
data.value: A closed Brep with normals facing out.

data.name: surfaceEnvironmentDescription
data.value: A Surface Environment upon which the Quelea will map their position for the calculation of Forces.

data.name: weightMultiplierDescription
data.value: The factor by which the force will be multiplied by.

data.name: viewForceDescription
data.value: Applies a force to move the Agent laterally away from any Agent that blocks its view.

data.name: attractForceDescription
data.value: Attracts a Quelea within the radius of the pt.

data.name: followPathForceDescription
data.value: Applies a Force to an Agent to move along and stay within a specified radius of a curve.

data.name: curveForFollowPathDescription
data.value: A curve representing the spine of the Path to follow.

data.name: pathRadiusDescription
data.value: The radius around which the Agents will try to stay within the Path.

data.name: predictionDistanceDescription
data.value: The distance the Agent will predict its future location at to determine if corrective steering should be applied.

data.name: pathTargetDistanceDescription
data.value: The distance along the path that the Agent will steer towards if determines corrective force needs to be applied.

data.name: applyDescription
data.value: If false, the Force will not be applied to the Quelea. This is useful for having Behaviors override Forces. Can also be used for only applying the force if the Quelea is within a certain area.

data.name: particleSettingsDescription
data.value: Constructs the settings for a particle.

data.name: particleDescription
data.value: A particle is a point that can be affected by forces that do not require a perception of its surroundings or used to supply settings for an agent.

data.name: queleaDescription
data.value: A Quelea which can be a Particle, Agent, or Vehicle.

data.name: vehicleDescription
data.value: A Vehicle with wheels that uses sensors to examine its' environment.

data.name: orientationDescription
data.value: A plane representing the orientation of the particle in the world.

data.name: visionAngleMultiplierErrorMessage
data.value: Vision Angle Multiplier must be between 0.0 and 1.0.

data.name: visionAngleMultiplierDescription
data.value: The factor by which the Agent's Vision Angle will be multiplied. The result will be used to determine the angle from the velocity that the agent will be able to see neighbors.

data.name: wrapDescription
data.value: If true, quelea will wrap around to other side of environment bounds.
